Do I have to register or get the application attested by any organisation for these compliances and how much is the fee

Short answer: for most SaaS apps, NO — you do NOT need to register or get attested by any authority to be “compliant.”
But for some certifications and regulated domains, YES, registration + fees apply.

Below is a clear, no-nonsense breakdown so you don’t overpay or overbuild.

🧭 Big Picture (Read This First)
Compliance Type	Registration Needed?	Fee?	Mandatory?
GDPR / UK GDPR	❌ No	£0	✅ Yes
Privacy / ToS	❌ No	£0	✅ Yes
PCI-DSS (via Stripe etc.)	❌ No	£0	✅ Yes
SOC 2	✅ Yes	£10k–£40k	❌ Optional
ISO 27001	✅ Yes	£5k–£25k	❌ Optional
HIPAA	❌ No	£0	Only if healthcare
EU AI Act	❌ (initially)	£0	Coming soon

👉 Compliance ≠ Certification
Compliance = you follow the rules
Certification = you pay someone to verify it

1️⃣ GDPR / UK GDPR — No Registration, No Fee

GDPR
UK GDPR

Do you need to register?

❌ NO (this is the biggest myth)

You self-declare compliance

Any fees?

❌ £0

When would money be involved?

If you hire consultants or lawyers (optional)

If you get fined for non-compliance (very expensive)

What regulators expect

Bottom-up compliance:

Privacy Policy

Data deletion/export

Security controls

Breach response

📌 Nobody “approves” your GDPR compliance in advance.

2️⃣ ICO Registration (UK Only – Small Fee)

Information Commissioner's Office

If you are UK-based, this is the ONLY mandatory registration most founders miss.

Do you need it?

✅ YES, if you:

store user data

run analytics

have email/password auth

Fee

£40–£60 per year (most startups)

Larger companies: up to £2,900/year

🔴 This is not GDPR certification
It’s a data protection fee, not approval.

3️⃣ PCI-DSS (Payments) — No Registration If You Use Stripe

PCI DSS

Do you need to register?

❌ NO, if:

You use Stripe / Paddle / Razorpay

You use hosted checkout

Fee?

❌ £0 (included in Stripe fees)

When DO you need registration?

🚨 Only if:

You store card numbers

You build your own payment gateway

(You should not.)

